scenes.label: *start
texts: I've never eaten anything so exquisite in all my life! What do you call this?!
Ramen! Fried rice! Delicioso!\nSorry, but can I get another helping?!
The place Oz chose was a tiny, dirty, old Chinese restaurant. It felt like it somewhere straight outta the 20th century.
If I'd been alone, I would've needed a whole lot of courage to come in here at all. It really didn't seem like a place with good food.
But once I saw how excited Momo was, I realized how off my assumption had been.
My own share of the ramen and fried rice was already in front of me.
This reminded me I hadn't eaten since yesterday afternoon. I scooped up some fried rice with the china spoon, excited for a mouthful of flavor.
It was oily, and super salty.
This was the opposite. It had a really light taste... Actually, it didn't taste like anything.
That was when my eyes met Oz's.
This place is known for its garlic chives and liver stir fry.

scenes.label: *load
texts: I looked over to see that very dish in front of both Oz and Nonno.
Oh man. I should've ordered that too...
Why did Momo like this so much, anyway?
This was kinda depressing. Now I had to eat this terrible ramen and fried rice.

scenes.label: *select1
texts: Oh? You're thinking I should Load?
Well, honestly, I'm with you on that one.
I Saved just in case Oz turned out to be an enemy, so I really didn't expect I'd be Loading for this kinda thing.
Oz and Nonno were already there when we walked in, just like the first time.
We already ordered somethin'. What are you havin'?
Garlic chives and liver stir fry.
Ah. I'll have the same, then.
People who order that here know what's good. Who told ya about that dish?
Hehe. The man looked baffled. This felt kinda good.
Our food arrived fast, and damn, Oz wasn't kidding about it.
Momo's reaction to it was the same, though: "delicioso" on repeat.

scenes.label: *mergeA
texts: With our plates almost empty, Nonno stood up and poked my arm.
Polly? Is that supposed to be me?
Nonno boldly grabbed her skirt and lifted it up.
Suddenly, two mechanical boom arms peeked out from under her skirt.
The right arm gripped Nonno by her waist, then sat her on the chair that the left arm had folded into.
The left one was wheeled, and started spinning in place while Nonno was sitting on it.
Cool, cool, molecule! I knew you'd say that!
I call it the "Beary-Easy!" I made it myself! It can even run! Its speed tops out at 40km/h!
She suddenly started fidgeting for some reason.
Hey, Polly. I'm not taken right now, so...who is Momom to you?
Hm? What are you talking about? Who's Momom?
Nonno glanced at Momo, who looked well-fed and satisfied.
You're kinda dense, aren'tcha? I'm asking if you're dating anyone right now.
Oh, so I guess she was one of those kids who's in a rush to grow up.
Nonno, act your age and stop trying to flirt with the guy.
I'm trying to be a hero, who helps anyone in need.
So, I, uh...got no time for women. G-got it?
Ohh! I knew you were cool, but not this cool!
Hell yeah, I am. If you're ever in need, just let me know, okay?
I put it on aaall the gadgets I make.
At least that fit her age.
If she'd given this to me as a peace offering, I had to respond in kind.
Come hang out at Symphony sometime. I'll make you a member of Nakano Symphonies.
Yeah. We got no cats, but you're always welcome.
YAY! I wanna go! I'm gonna go! Today!
Hey, stop playing around with children.
I'm not a child. I'm a lady.
Nonno returned to her seat, satisfied.
Is she your daughter or something? You don't look related.
Hell no. She's just a freeloader.
Hey! You should be glad you get to support a lady like me!
Just eat. You haven't finished yet.
Their situation seemed complicated, but this probably wasn't the time to ask about it.
So, let's get down to business.
I beckoned Momo over. She tensed up, but came closer.
We'd been in the restaurant for like 20 minutes, but there hadn't been a single other customer. Pretty weird for a weekday lunch time.

scenes.label: *chk_ev
texts: I was beginning to understand why Oz had picked this place for us to chat.
Tell me about the guys who were after Momo. I know it's the army, but who do they serve?
They're the SFG. Special Forces Group. A secretive unit of elite soldiers.
Why would a group like that...?
They're not like a normal unit. They're only mobilized when the operation's above the law.
Odds are that they got their orders from real high up in the government.
And it was a covert operation too. They weren't allowed to make a scene.
Thanks to you though, that didn't really work out.
Heh. Serves them right. Now they'll know not to mess with me.
I'm not bullshitting you. I never say anything I can't back up.
...Anyway, everything related to yesterday's thing has been deleted.
And it's not just what the SFG did. Basically everything about everyone involved is gone too.
And that includes my crimes, huh?
The army couldn't have done that themselves. Odds are someone in Nagatacho was involved.
It was starting to sound like this guy had connections in the government, as well as the police.
So, what's the deal between you and the army?
...I'm a jack of all trades. I take jobs and conduct investigations.
Yeah, that sounded cool. Way better than hacker work, anyway.
Right now, I'm on a job investigating the Gai Institution.
That's...the place where the Gai <tips,27,QCDC> is kept, right?
Gai was one of the most powerful QCDCs in Japan, no...in the whole world.
From what I could remember, it was kept at some facility in Uminomori.
What if I told you that the SFG guards the place 24/7?
He took out a piece of paper and placed it on the counter.
Not at all. You care about security, huh?
The best way to prevent data theft was to avoid putting any data on the internet in the first place.
The photo had been taken with a ultra-telephoto lens, and it showed soldiers guarding something. Tatted baldy-builder was among them.
Ground Self-Defense Forces, Major Graham Kingly. Captain of the SFG.
They're protecting the program that uses most of the Gai QCDC's resources.
Though, officially, research on the program was frozen eight years ago.
Its name is "GAIA." It's an Earth Simulator generated by a quantum supercomputer.
Oz showed me another photo. It looked like a cut-out from an old newspaper.
12 years ago, Project GAIA began as a joint effort between MEXT, METI, and MOD. Gai Institution was established for that purpose.
The project's goal was to develop the quantum supercomputer, Gai QCDC, and the Earth simulator, GAIA.
It's possible to perfectly predict the future using that simulator. You can't even fathom the ways Japan would benefit from that.
At the time, the Earth Simulator race was at its global peak. Everyone wanted a magic box that'd show them the future.
I know. But then they realized that "knowledge of the future is more dangerous than nukes" and stopped, right?
If the simulations were advanced enough, they could even allow access to highly classified information, like other countries' nuclear codes.
That was the kind of thing these simulators were capable of.
That's why various countries held a meeting and agreed to cease development of their Earth Simulators. It was a pretty big deal back then.
Yeah. There were opposition movements everywhere.
And just like the other Earth Simulators, development of GAIA came to a stop.
The Gai Institution continued to exist in order to operate QCDC, but the topic of GAIA itself became taboo.
But what country's gonna give up on tech that lets them see the future? They're still working on their Earth Simulators. Just in secret.
And Japan is no exception, huh?
There was another reason why development on GAIA resumed, though.
This one seemed like a screen capture from some news show.
It happened shortly after the Sad Morning. Some hacker went and hacked into the Gai Institution.
He took full control of the management systems, and stole all the info on GAIA as it was back then.
If this stuff was true, it really didn't seem like something people should be discussing so openly in some rundown Chinese restaurant.
The Ministry of Defense was in charge of caretakin' GAIA while it was frozen, so the whole thing left them with egg on their face.
They were clearly desperate to find the culprit.
A godlike hacker like that would never let himself be caught.
You'd think that, but he went and left evidence on purpose, so they found him right away.
So he was just showing off his skills? What an asshole.
Anyway, the army broke into his place, fully armed, and what they found was...
The bow-tie boy from the chopper!
Despite being just 12 years old at the time, and surrounded by armed men, he insisted that they hire him so he could complete GAIA.
The government went on to make him the Gai Institution's head researcher, and he resumed development on GAIA in secret.
They figured having him develop GAIA was more beneficial to them than eliminating him and wasting his skills.
So GAIA's still under development, and the army's secret squad is guarding it, huh?
Not entirely correct. GAIA's probably complete by now.
The SFG only took up posts outside the Gai Institution this year.
There was also some big shot who disappeared right before all that. The AOAB Director-General of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
His last known location was at the Gai Institution.
Well, that kinda reeked. Assuming Oz wasn't bullshitting me, anyway.
The Gai QCDC was known to the public, and provided calculation services and the like.
Results of research programs using the Gai QCDC would be broadcast on the news sometimes.
But GAIA was something so classified that the public wasn't even told that its development had resumed.
And the army was there to keep anything about it from leaking out.
So basically, GAIA was at the heart of a huge conspiracy.
What I wanna know is why this secret squad of elite soldiers...
Oz shifted his gaze to Momo, who was listening to our conversation.
I gave you my info. Now it's your turn.
Did any of those names I mentioned ring any bells?
Then why were the SFG after you?
I'd convinced her that if she wanted to learn anything from Oz, she would have to share something too.
I nodded. Momo gathered her resolve, sighed, and looked at us.
I'm about to tell you something very important. Please keep all of it secret.
